The paper discusses the problem of learning structures of probabilistic graphical models, which is a central problem in modern AI research. The paper specifically focuses on the score-based setting for Bayesian networks and proposes an optimal approach based on integer programming. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses computational complexity and polytopes, which are topics related to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also involves exhaustive computation, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses facets of polytopes, which is related to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
